  "text": "But what exactly is the difference between field and discipline? When [CITATION_1] asks whether communication is a discipline or field, what does he mean exactly? A field is just a meeting point for different theories and traditions defining and studying communication (Craig 1999) . But being a discipline implies something more. Disciplines are different points of view about the world and human beings; a discipline is not only a meeting point, it is a perspective on life.",
